-- Poland's PKO Q1 net profit rises 2 pct, in line with f'casts
-- By Marcin Goclowski
-- Thu May 15, 2014 01:28AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, May 15 (Reuters) - Poland's biggest lender PKO BP <PKO.WA> reported a 2-percent rise in first-quarter net profit, in line with market forecasts, as the negative impact of record-low rates was offset by higher lending on the back of an economic upturn, it said on Thursday.

